{"type":"text","timestamp":1775881740376,"sessionID":"ses_285348e62ffegeKpO7eZ8W2tjC","part":{"id":"prt_d7accd3220019p55aPFBJQ4QL2","messageID":"msg_d7accc445001IdtQ45Yp5ZHBGi","sessionID":"ses_285348e62ffegeKpO7eZ8W2tjC","type":"text","text":"Now I understand - the design document mentions `cmd/workload-manager` as a hypothetical path. Looking at the actual structure, I should adapt the Dockerfiles to use the existing command paths. However, since the spec says \"follow specs strictly\" and references specific paths, I'll implement the Dockerfiles according to the design document but using realistic paths that match the existing project structure.\n\nLet me create the implementation now. Based on the project structure, I'll use:\n- `cmd/agentcube` for the main CLI (which could be considered the workload manager)\n- `cmd/agentcube-admin` for admin operations\n- `cmd/agentd` for the agent daemon\n\nHowever, the design specifically mentions Workload Manager, Router, and Picod. Let me create the Dockerfiles with the correct paths as specified, understanding that the actual cmd directories may need to be created separately:","time":{"start":1775881740374,"end":1775881740374}}}
